  "body": "when we use a bytecode which contains an \"infinite loop\" to test the go-ethereum, the **binary evm** will keep running and consume the memory and CPU resources until the **out of memory** and **crash**.  for example, we use this simple contract as follows,\r\n![Screenshot from 2020-05-31 22-36-52](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/13298978/83708346-aa1e6500-a64e-11ea-83d3-2726b4cb1aa0.png)\r\nThe command is **evm --debug --json --code run** \r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.9.11`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\nbincode = \"\"\r\n\r\ninputdata = \"f8a8fd6d\"\r\n\r\n",
